The Federal Road Safety Corps (FRSC) has appointed Assistant Corps Marshal ( ACM) Meshach Jatau as the new Zonal Commanding Officer for Osun, Oyo and Ekiti. This is contained in a statement issued by the Zonal Public Education Officer, Kolawole Alabi, on Tuesday in Osogbo. The new zonal commander has held various command and operational positions before his appointment. He was Registrar FRSC Academy, Sector Commander in Abia and Rivers, Commandant, Inspectorate Training School, Director of Studies, FRSC Command and Staff College, and Principal Corps Officer to the Corps Marshal. Jatau is a Fellow of the Nigeria Army War College and a member of Japan International Cooperation Agency. (NAN)